==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roaring twenties
<hw>Roar"ing twen"ties</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>The decade from 1920 to
1929; -- so called because of the occurrence of a prosperous economy and
rapid changes in sociological mores as exemplified by speakeasies, the
popularity of fast cars and jazz, and the boisterous unconventional
behavior of young adults in that period. See also <er>flapper</er>,
<er>speakeasy</er>, and second <er>prohibition</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roaringly</ent>⟦br⟧
